title: Reddit PWND Wall Street, Robo Biden 1.28.21
itunes:title: Reddit PWND Wall Street, Robo Biden 1.28.21
description:
In episode 800, Jack and Miles are joined by comedian and writer Mike Drucker to discuss Reddit coming for Wall Street, Trump's impeachment, Fox News pretending to care, the New James Bond movie, the Ellen show ending, robot presidents at Disneyland, and more!

FOOTNOTES:

  1. Silent Hill 2 by Mike Drucker
  2. How WallStreetBets Pushed GameStop Shares to the Moon
  3. What’s next for Trump’s trial? What we know after most GOP senators voted against
  4. Hannity dabbling in anti-vax: "I've been telling my friends I'm getting the vaccine. Half of them agree and the other half think I'm absolutely nuts. I don't know who to listen to."
  5. ‘No Time to Die’ Delays Release Date Again
  6. Bond fans ask for No Time to Die delay due to coronavirus
  7. Bond 25: With Danny Boyle’s Exit, the Latest 007 Could Miss Its Release Date
  8. Danny Boyle’s James Bond Was ‘Crazy, Madcap, and Extraordinary,’ Says 007 Crew Member
  9. Daniel Craig to Undergo Ankle Surgery After Bond 25 Set Injury, Film’s Release Date Not Changing
  10. Explosion on Bond 25 set causes injury, damage to studio
  11. Cary Fukunaga Addresses Bond 25 Rumor He’s Skipping Filming and Causing Crew Backlash
  12. Grace Jones ‘quits’ Bond 25 ‘moments after arriving on set’, reports claim
  13. James Bond Film ‘No Time to Die’ Explored $600 Million Sale to Streaming Services
  14. Does Bond’s product placement go too far?
  15. Bond film delays are reportedly causing product placement havoc for brands
  16. The Era of the Ellen DeGeneres Show Might Be Coming to an End
  17. Disney World Plans Audio-Animatronic Version Of Joe Biden For Its Hall Of Presidents
  18. CONFIRMED: Disney Announces Addition of Joe Biden Audio-Animatronic to The Hall of Presidents at the Magic Kingdom
  19. Trump is leaving office, but will he be leaving Disney's Hall of Presidents?
  20. A Deep Dive Into the Bloody Battle for 'Disney’s America', the Theme Park That Never Was
  21. WATCH: Cal Tjader - Aquarius
